1️⃣ First Finish Database Tables

Before running Filament resource commands, you must have these tables in the database:

roles
users
menus
role_menu_access
sellers
buyers
items
sales

So first you should:

Create migrations

Paste the migration code

Run

php artisan migrate

After this, your database will be ready.

2️⃣ Then Run Filament Resource Commands

After migrations, run these commands one by one.

php artisan make:filament-resource Role
php artisan make:filament-resource User
php artisan make:filament-resource Seller
php artisan make:filament-resource Buyer
php artisan make:filament-resource Item
php artisan make:filament-resource Sale
3️⃣ What Happens When You Run These Commands

Example command:

php artisan make:filament-resource Seller

Laravel will create these files automatically:

app
 └ Filament
     └ Resources
         SellerResource.php
         SellerResource
             Pages
                 CreateSeller.php
                 EditSeller.php
                 ListSellers.php

These files create:

✔ Sellers list page
✔ Create seller form
✔ Edit seller page
✔ Delete option

All automatically inside the Filament admin panel.

4️⃣ What You Will See After Running Server

Run:

php artisan serve

Then open:

http://localhost:8000/admin

You will see something like this sidebar:

Dashboard
Users
Roles
Sellers
Buyers
Items
Sales

